<TITLE> Knit factory owners, workers demonstrate unity </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narayanganj, Dec 18 (bdnews24.com)  State minister for home Shamsul Huq Tuku on Friday urged knitwear factory owners and workers to remain cautious about recurrence of unrest in their premises. "You (owners and workers) are both equally responsible for uninterrupted production in this sector," he said while speaking as chief guest at the knitwear factory workers' festival in Narayanganj Osmani Stadium. "Owners are responsible to pay workers' salaries in time and workers must keep wheels of economic wheels running through the maintaining production." "Remember, workers and owners well related, and want to boost output together." "We must keep a watchful eye all the time in preventing any conflict or sabotage in knitwear industries." Bangladesh Knitwear Manufacturers and Exporters Association hosted the festival. Two hundred various factory workers performed at the festival, which was featured by singing, dancing, drama, magic and fashion show. BKMEA president Fazlul Hoque said, "We don't like to satisfy workers only with salaries and allowances, also with incentives." "We want to strengthen friendly ties between workers and owners." "Bangladesh ranks third in the world in knitwear exports. We, workers and owners are united in facing the ongoing global economic recession." "We will take the lead in world knitwear exports in a few years." Keeping this in view, this festival was arranged for the second time, he added. Bangladesh exports knitwear products to over 100 countries across the world. It earned $6.46b in fiscal 2008-09. China and Turkey take the first and second position respectively in knitwear exports in the world. bd
